# Untitled UI only

All UI in `email-lever-studio/client` must use the vendored **Untitled UI** design system. Do not introduce other component libraries or hand-rolled controls when an Untitled UI equivalent exists.

## Imports

| Need | Import from |
|------|-------------|
| Components | `@ui/components/...` |
| Icons | `@untitledui/icons` |
| Utils inside untitled-ui | `@/utils/...` (only inside `client/src/untitled-ui/`) |

`@ui` resolves to `client/src/untitled-ui/`. Browse that folder before building custom UI.

## Required patterns

```tsx
// ✅ Button
import { Button } from '@ui/components/base/buttons/button'
import { Plus } from '@untitledui/icons'

<Button size="xs" color="tertiary" iconLeading={Plus} aria-label="New campaign" />

// ✅ Input, Badge, Avatar, SlideoutMenu, NavItemBase, etc.
import { Input } from '@ui/components/base/input/input'
import { SlideoutMenu } from '@ui/components/application/slideout-menus/slideout-menu'
```

```tsx
// ❌ Do not use
<button className="...">...</button>
import { Button } from 'some-other-ui-lib'
```

## Styling

- Use Untitled UI semantic tokens: `bg-primary`, `text-tertiary`, `ring-secondary`, `text-display-xs`, etc.
- Match existing dashboard patterns (`ToolbarActionButton`, drawers, `CampaignSidebar`).
- Plain layout elements (`div`, `p`, `ul`) are fine; interactive and branded controls must be Untitled UI components.

## Before adding UI

1. Search `client/src/untitled-ui/components/` for an existing component.
2. Reuse application-level wrappers in `client/src/dashboard/components/` when they already wrap Untitled UI.
3. Only create a new local component when nothing in Untitled UI fits—and compose it from Untitled UI primitives.
